    plt.figure()  # Create a new figure for each line plot
    sns.lineplot(x='year', y=column, data=df_month_location_line, label=column)
    
    # Calculate regression line
    x = df_month_location_line['year']
    y = df_month_location_line[column]
    slope, intercept = np.polyfit(x, y, 1)
    plt.plot(x, slope*x + intercept, color='red', label='Regression line')
    
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel(column)
    plt.title(f'Line Graph - {column}')
    plt.legend()

# Display the plots
plt.show()

# Define Dash app
app = dash.Dash(__name__)

# Define app layout
app.layout = html.Div([
    html.H1("Data Visualization"),
    
    # Radio buttons for selecting data type
    dcc.RadioItems(
        id='data-type-radio',
        options=[
            {'label': 'Year', 'value': 'year'},
            {'label': 'Month', 'value': 'month'},
            {'label': 'Season', 'value': 'season'}
        ],
        value='year',  # Default value
        labelStyle={'display': 'inline-block'}
    ),
    
    # Dropdown for selecting station_id
    dcc.Dropdown(
        id='station-dropdown',
        options=[{'label': str(station), 'value': station} for station in df_month_location['station_id'].unique()],
        value=df_month_location['station_id'].unique()[0]
    ),
    
    # Dropdown for selecting x column
    dcc.Dropdown(
        id='x-column-dropdown',
        options=[{'label': col, 'value': col} for col in x_columns],
        value=x_columns[0]
    ),
    
    # Line plot
    dcc.Graph(id='line-plot')
])

# Callback to update line plot based on selected options
@app.callback(
    Output('line-plot', 'figure'),
    [Input('data-type-radio', 'value'),
     Input('station-dropdown', 'value'),
     Input('x-column-dropdown', 'value')]
)
def update_line_plot(data_type, station_id, selected_x):
    if data_type == 'year':
        df = df_year_location[df_year_location['station_id'] == station_id]
        x_label = 'Year'
    elif data_type == 'month':
        df = df_month_location[(df_month_location['station_id'] == station_id) & (df_month_location['month'] == 1)]  # Selecting January for demonstration
        x_label = 'Month'
    else:  # Season
        df = df_season_location[(df_season_location['station_id'] == station_id) & (df_season_location['season'] == 'Winter')]  # Selecting Winter for demonstration
        x_label = 'Season'
    
    # Create trace for line plot
    trace = go.Scatter(
        x=df[x_label],
        y=df[selected_x],
        mode='lines+markers',
        name=selected_x
    )
    
    # Layout for line plot
    layout = go.Layout(
        title=f"{selected_x} Analysis",
        xaxis={'title': x_label},
        yaxis={'title': selected_x}
    )
    
    return {'data': [trace], 'layout': layout}

# Run the app
if __name__ == '__main__':
    app.run_server(debug=True)

app = dash.Dash(__name__)

# Define available x-axis variables
x_columns = ['DTR (Diurnal Temperature Range)', 'FD (Frost Days)', 'PRCPTOT (Total Precipitation)',
             'R10mm (Days with ≥ 10mm rain)', 'R20mm (Days with ≥ 20mm rain)', 'R5mm (Days with ≥ 5mm rain)',
             'Rx1day (Wettest day)', 'Rx5day (Wettest 5-Day Period)', 'SDII (Average Daily Rainfall Intensity)',
             'SU (Summer Days)', 'TN10p (Cold Nights)', 'TN90p (Warm Nights)', 'TNn (Coldest Night)',
             'TNx (Warmest Night)', 'TR (Tropical Nights)', 'TX10p (Cold Days)', 'TX90p (Warm Days)',
             'TXn (Coldest Day)', 'TXx (Warmest Day)', 'n_maxdy', 'n_mindy', 'n_rain']

# Define app layout
app.layout = html.Div([
    html.H1("Data Visualization Dashboard"),

    # Radio buttons for selecting data source
    html.Div([
        html.Label("Select Data Source:"),
        dcc.RadioItems(
            id='data-source-radio',
            options=[
                {'label': 'Year', 'value': 'year'},
                {'label': 'Season', 'value': 'season'},
                {'label': 'Month', 'value': 'month'}
            ],
            value='year',
            labelStyle={'display': 'inline-block'}
        ),
    ], style={'margin-bottom': '20px'}),

    # Dropdown for selecting station_id
    html.Div(id='station-dropdown-container', children=[
        html.Label("Select Station:"),
        dcc.Dropdown(
            id='station-dropdown',
            options=[{'label': str(station), 'value': station} for station in df_month_location['station_id'].unique()],
            value=df_month_location['station_id'].iloc[0]  # Default value
        )
    ], style={'margin-bottom': '20px'}),

    # Dropdown for selecting x column
    html.Div([
        html.Label("Select X Column:"),
        dcc.Dropdown(
            id='x-column-dropdown',
            options=[{'label': col, 'value': col} for col in x_columns],
            value=x_columns[0]  # Default value
        ),
    ], style={'margin-bottom': '20px'}),

    # Line graph
    dcc.Graph(id='line-plot')
])


# Callback to update dropdown options based on selected data source
@app.callback(
    Output('station-dropdown-container', 'children'),
    [Input('data-source-radio', 'value')]
)
def update_dropdown(data_source):
    if data_source == 'year':
        options = [{'label': str(station), 'value': station} for station in df_year_location['station_id'].unique()]
    elif data_source == 'season':
        options = [{'label': str(station), 'value': station} for station in df_season_location['station_id'].unique()]
    elif data_source == 'month':
        options = [{'label': str(station), 'value': station} for station in df_month_location['station_id'].unique()]
    else:
        options = []
    return [
        html.Label("Select Station:"),
        dcc.Dropdown(
            id='station-dropdown',
            options=options,
            value=options[0]['value'] if options else None
        )
    ]


# Callback to update line plot based on dropdown selections
@app.callback(
    Output('line-plot', 'figure'),
    [Input('data-source-radio', 'value'),
     Input('station-dropdown', 'value'),
     Input('x-column-dropdown', 'value')]
)
def update_line_plot(data_source, station_id, selected_x):
    if data_source == 'year':
        df = df_year_location[df_year_location['station_id'] == station_id]
    elif data_source == 'season':
        df = df_season_location[df_season_location['station_id'] == station_id]
    elif data_source == 'month':
        df = df_month_location[df_month_location['station_id'] == station_id]
    else:
        df = pd.DataFrame()

    if not df.empty:
        # Calculate mean for selected x column grouped by year
        avg_values = df.groupby('year')[selected_x].mean().reset_index()

        # Create trace for line plot
        trace = go.Scatter(
            x=avg_values['year'],
            y=avg_values[selected_x],
            mode='lines+markers',
            name=selected_x
        )

        # Layout for line plot
        layout = go.Layout(
            title=f"{selected_x} Analysis",
            xaxis={'title': 'Year'},
            yaxis={'title': selected_x}
        )

        return {'data': [trace], 'layout': layout}
    else:
        return {}


# Run the app
if __name__ == '__main__':
    app.run_server(debug=True)

def update_line_plot(data_source, station_id, selected_x):
    if data_source == 'year':
        df = df_year_location.copy()

        df = df_season_location.copy()

def update_line_plot(data_source, station_id, selected_x, selected_months):
    if data_source == 'year':
        df = df_year_location.copy()
    elif data_source == 'season':
        df = df_season_location.copy()
    elif data_source == 'month':
        df = df_month_location.copy()
    else:
        df = pd.DataFrame()

    if station_id:
        df = df[df['station_id'].isin(station_id)]

    if selected_months:
        df = df[df['month'].isin(selected_months)]

    if not df.empty:
        # Calculate mean for selected x column grouped by year
        avg_values = df.groupby('year')[selected_x].mean().reset_index()

        # Create trace for line plot
        trace = go.Scatter(

            mode='lines+markers',
            name=selected_x
        )

        # Layout for line plot
        layout = go.Layout(
            title=f"{selected_x} Analysis",
            xaxis={'title': 'Year'},
            yaxis={'title': selected_x}
        )

        return {'data': [trace], 'layout': layout}
    else:
        return {}

import base64

# Assuming df_location, df_month_location, df_season_location, df_year_location are already defined

app = dash.Dash(__name__)

x_columns = ['DTR (Diurnal Temperature Range)', 'FD (Frost Days)', 'PRCPTOT (Total Precipitation)',
             'R10mm (Days with ≥ 10mm rain)', 'R20mm (Days with ≥ 20mm rain)', 'R5mm (Days with ≥ 5mm rain)',
             'Rx1day (Wettest day)', 'Rx5day (Wettest 5-Day Period)', 'SDII (Average Daily Rainfall Intensity)',
             'SU (Summer Days)', 'TN10p (Cold Nights)', 'TN90p (Warm Nights)', 'TNn (Coldest Night)',
             'TNx (Warmest Night)', 'TR (Tropical Nights)', 'TX10p (Cold Days)', 'TX90p (Warm Days)',
             'TXn (Coldest Day)', 'TXx (Warmest Day)', 'n_maxdy', 'n_mindy', 'n_rain']

app.layout = html.Div([
    html.H1("Visualization of Climate Indices"),
    dcc.RadioItems(
        id='data-source-radio',
        options=[
            {'label': 'Year', 'value': 'year'},
            {'label': 'Season', 'value': 'season'},
            {'label': 'Month', 'value': 'month'}
        ],
        value='year',
        labelStyle={'display': 'inline-block'}
    ),
    dcc.Dropdown(
        id='station-dropdown',
        options=[{'label': station, 'value': station} for station in df_location['station_id'].unique()],
        multi=True,
        placeholder="Select Station(s)"
    ),
    dcc.Dropdown(
        id='x-column-dropdown',
        options=[{'label': x, 'value': x} for x in x_columns],
        value=x_columns[0]
    ),
    dcc.Graph(id='line-plot'),
    html.Iframe(id='station-map', height='600', width='100%', style={'border': 'none'}),
])

@app.callback(
    Output('line-plot', 'figure'),
    [Input('data-source-radio', 'value'),
     Input('station-dropdown', 'value'),
     Input('x-column-dropdown', 'value')]
)
def update_line_plot(data_source, station_ids, selected_x):
    # Placeholder for actual data filtering based on selected station and data source
    # Assuming df has columns ['year', selected_x] for simplicity
    if station_ids is None:
        return go.Figure()
    
    # Select the correct dataframe based on the data_source value
    if data_source == 'year':
        df = df_year_location.copy()
    elif data_source == 'season':
        df = df_season_location.copy()
    else:  # 'month'
        df = df_month_location.copy()
    
    df_filtered = df[df['station_id'].isin(station_ids)]
    
    # Group by year and calculate mean for the selected X column
    df_grouped = df_filtered.groupby('year')[selected_x].mean().reset_index()

    fig = go.Figure(data=go.Scatter(x=df_grouped['year'], y=df_grouped[selected_x],
                                    mode='lines+markers', name=selected_x))
    fig.update_layout(title=f"{selected_x} over Time",
                      xaxis_title='Year',
                      yaxis_title=selected_x)
    return fig

@app.callback(
    Output('station-map', 'srcDoc'),
    [Input('station-dropdown', 'value')]
)
def update_map(station_ids):
    # Create a map centered on the average latitude and longitude
    map_center = df_location[['Latitude', 'Longitude']].mean().values.tolist()
    m = folium.Map(location=map_center, zoom_start=2)
    
    # Filter df_location for selected stations
    if station_ids:
        df_filtered = df_location[df_location['station_id'].isin(station_ids)]
    else:
        df_filtered = df_location

    for _, row in df_filtered.iterrows():
        folium.Marker([row['Latitude'], row['Longitude']],
                      popup=f"Station: {row['station_id']}").add_to(m)
    
    # Convert Folium map to HTML
    map_html = m._repr_html_()
    return map_html

if __name__ == '__main__':
    app.run_server(port=8503)

     Input('x-column-dropdown', 'value'),
     Input('data-source-radio', 'value')]
)
def update_map_plot(station_ids, selected_x, data_source):
    if data_source == 'year':
        df_data = df_year_location
    elif data_source == 'season':
        df_data = df_season_location
    else:  # 'month'
        df_data = df_month_location

    df_merged = pd.merge(df_location, df_data[['station_id', selected_x]], on='station_id', how='inner')

    if station_ids:
        df_filtered = df_merged[df_merged['station_id'].isin(station_ids)]
    else:
        df_filtered = df_merged

    df_filtered['normalized_size'] = df_filtered[selected_x] / df_filtered[selected_x].max() * 50

    fig = go.Figure(go.Scattergeo(
        lon = df_filtered['Longitude'],
        lat = df_filtered['Latitude'],
        text = df_filtered['station_id'],
        marker = dict(
            size = df_filtered['normalized_size'],
            color = 'blue',
            line_color='black',
            line_width=0.5,
            sizemode = 'diameter'
        )
    ))

    fig.update_layout(
        title='Station Locations and Selected Index in Ireland',
        geo=dict(
            showland=True,
            landcolor="rgb(217, 217, 217)",
            countrycolor="rgb(204, 204, 204)",
            showcountries=True,
            center=dict(
                lat=53.4,  # Approximate central latitude of Ireland
                lon=-8.0   # Approximate central longitude of Ireland
            ),
            projection_scale=5,  # Adjusts the zoom
            projection_type='mercator'
        )
    )

    return fig

# Callback to update line plot based on dropdown selections
@app.callback(
    Output('line-plot', 'figure'),
    [Input('data-source-radio', 'value'),
     Input('station-dropdown', 'value'),
     Input('x-column-dropdown', 'value'),
     Input('month-dropdown', 'value'),
     Input('season-dropdown', 'value')]
)
def update_line_plot(data_source, station_id, selected_x, selected_month, selected_season):
    if data_source == 'year':
        df = df_year_location.copy()
    elif data_source == 'season':
        df = df_season_location.copy()
    elif data_source == 'month':
        df = df_month_location.copy()
    else:
        df = pd.DataFrame()

    if station_id:
        df = df[df['station_id'].isin(station_id)]

    if not df.empty:
        if data_source == 'month':
            df_filtered = df[df['month'] == selected_month]
        elif data_source == 'season':
            df_filtered = df[df['season'] == selected_season]
        else:
            df_filtered = df

        # Calculate mean for selected x column grouped by year
        avg_values = df_filtered.groupby('year')[selected_x].mean().reset_index()

        # Create trace for line plot
        trace = go.Scatter(
            x=avg_values['year'],
            y=avg_values[selected_x],
            mode='lines+markers',
            name=selected_x
        )

        # Layout for line plot
        layout = go.Layout(
            title=f"{selected_x} Analysis",
            xaxis={'title': 'Year'},
            yaxis={'title': selected_x}
        )

        return {'data': [trace], 'layout': layout}
    else:
        return {}

@app.callback(

# Create the Leaflet map component
@app.callback(
    Output("leaflet-map", "children"),
    [Input('data-source-radio', 'value')]
)
def update_map(data_source):
    if data_source == 'year':
        df = df_year_location.copy()
    elif data_source == 'season':
        df = df_season_location.copy()
    elif data_source == 'month':
        df = df_month_location.copy()
    else:
        df = pd.DataFrame()

    if not df.empty:
        # Create a map centered around the Republic of Ireland
        map_irish = dl.Map(style={'width': '1000px', 'height': '500px'}, center=[53.4129, -8.2439], zoom=7, children=[])

        # Add markers for each location in df_location
        for index, row in df.iterrows():
            marker = dl.Marker(position=[row['Latitude'], row['Longitude']], children=[
                dl.Tooltip(row['station_id'])
            ])
            map_irish.children += [marker]

        return map_irish
    else:
        return html.Div()

@app.callback(

    [Input('data-source-radio', 'value'),
     Input('station-dropdown', 'value'),
     Input('x-column-dropdown', 'value'),
     Input('month-dropdown', 'value'),
     Input('season-dropdown', 'value')]
)
def update_line_plot(data_source, station_id, selected_x, selected_month, selected_season):
    if data_source == 'year':
        df = df_year_location.copy()
    elif data_source == 'season':
        df = df_season_location.copy()
    elif data_source == 'month':
        df = df_month_location.copy()
    else:
        df = pd.DataFrame()

    if station_id:
        df = df[df['station_id'].isin(station_id)]

    if not df.empty:
        if data_source == 'month':
            df_filtered = df[df['month'] == selected_month]
        elif data_source == 'season':
            df_filtered = df[df['season'] == selected_season]
        else:
            df_filtered = df

        # Calculate mean for selected x column grouped by year
        avg_values = df_filtered.groupby('year')[selected_x].mean().reset_index()

        # Create trace for line plot
        trace = go.Scatter(
            x=avg_values['year'],
            y=avg_values[selected_x],
            mode='lines+markers',
            name=selected_x
        )

        # Layout for line plot
        layout = go.Layout(
            title=f"{selected_x} Analysis",
            xaxis={'title': 'Year'},
            yaxis={'title': selected_x}
        )

        return {'data': [trace], 'layout': layout}
    else:
        return {}

        df = pd.DataFrame()

    if not df.empty:
        # Create a Folium map centered around the Republic of Ireland
        map_irish = folium.Map(location=[53.4129, -8.2439], zoom_start=7)

        # Add markers for each location in df_location
        marker_cluster = MarkerCluster().add_to(map_irish)
        for index, row in df.iterrows():
            folium.Marker(location=[row['Latitude'], row['Longitude']], popup=row['station_id']).add_to(marker_cluster)

        # Convert Folium map to HTML
        map_html = map_irish.get_root().render()

        return html.Iframe(srcDoc=map_html, style={"width": "100%", "height": "500px"})
    else:
        return html.Div("No data available")

@app.callback(
    Output('line-plot', 'figure'),
    [Input('x-column-dropdown', 'value'),
     Input('station-dropdown', 'value')]
)
def update_line_plot(selected_x, station_id):
    # Placeholder DataFrame if no data source is selected
    df = pd.DataFrame()

    if station_id:
        df = df[df['station_id'].isin(station_id)]

    if selected_month:
        df = df[df['month'] == selected_month]

    if selected_season:
        df = df[df['season'] == selected_season]

    # Create line plot
    fig = go.Figure()

    for station in df['station_id'].unique():
        df_station = df[df['station_id'] == station]
        fig.add_trace(go.Scatter(x=df_station['year'], y=df_station[selected_x], mode='lines+markers', name=station))

    fig.update_layout(title=f'{selected_x} over Time',
                      xaxis_title='Year',
                      yaxis_title=selected_x,
                      template='plotly_dark')

    return fig

# Callback to update line plot based on dropdown selections
@app.callback(
    Output('line-plot', 'figure'),
    [Input('data-source-radio', 'value'),
     Input('station-dropdown', 'value'),
     Input('x-column-dropdown', 'value'),
     Input('month-dropdown', 'value'),
     Input('season-dropdown', 'value')]
)
def update_line_plot(data_source, station_id, selected_x, selected_month, selected_season):
    if data_source == 'year':
        df = df_year_location.copy()
    elif data_source == 'season':
        df = df_season_location.copy()
    elif data_source == 'month':
        df = df_month_location.copy()
    else:
        df = pd.DataFrame()

    if station_id:
        df = df[df['station_id'].isin(station_id)]

    if not df.empty:
        if data_source == 'month':
            df_filtered = df[df['month'] == selected_month]
        elif data_source == 'season':
            df_filtered = df[df['season'] == selected_season]
        else:
            df_filtered = df

        # Calculate mean for selected x column grouped by year
        avg_values = df_filtered.groupby('year')[selected_x].mean().reset_index()

        # Create trace for line plot
        trace = go.Scatter(
            x=avg_values['year'],
            y=avg_values[selected_x],
            mode='lines+markers',
            name=selected_x
        )

        # Layout for line plot
        layout = go.Layout(
            title=f"{selected_x} Analysis",
            xaxis={'title': 'Year'},
            yaxis={'title': selected_x}
        )

        return {'data': [trace], 'layout': layout}
    else:
        return {}

    Output("leaflet-map", "children"),
    [Input('data-source-radio', 'value')]
)
def update_map(data_source):
    if data_source == 'year':
        df = df_year_location.copy()
    elif data_source == 'season':
        df = df_season_location.copy()
    elif data_source == 'month':
        df = df_month_location.copy()
    else:
        df = pd.DataFrame()

    if not df.empty:
        # Create a Folium map centered around the Republic of Ireland
        map_irish = folium.Map(location=[53.4129, -8.2439], zoom_start=7)

        # Add markers for each location in df_location
        marker_cluster = MarkerCluster().add_to(map_irish)
        for index, row in df.iterrows():
            folium.Marker(location=[row['Latitude'], row['Longitude']], popup=row['station_id']).add_to(marker_cluster)

        # Convert Folium map to HTML
        map_html = map_irish.get_root().render()

        return html.Iframe(srcDoc=map_html, style={"width": "100%", "height": "500px"})
    else:
        return html.Div("No data available")

    app.run_server(debug=True)

    if station_ids:
        df_filtered = df[df['station_id'].isin(station_ids)]
        if data_source == 'month' and selected_month is not None:
            df_filtered = df_filtered[df_filtered['month'] == selected_month]
        elif data_source == 'season' and selected_season is not None:
            df_filtered = df_filtered[df_filtered['season'] == selected_season]
        
        markers = []
        for station_id in station_ids:
            station_data = df_filtered[df_filtered['station_id'] == station_id]
            if not station_data.empty:
                avg_value = station_data[selected_x].mean()
                lat, lon = station_data.iloc[0][['Latitude', 'Longitude']]
                markers.append(dl.Marker(position=[lat, lon], children=[
                    dl.Tooltip(f"{station_id}: {avg_value:.2f}")
                ]))
        return markers
    return []

        return station_options, season_options, {}
    else:  # month
        month_options = [{'label': m, 'value': m} for m in df_month_location['month'].unique()]
        return station_options, month_options, {}

# Callback to update graph and map
@app.callback(
    [Output('climate-graph', 'figure'),
     Output('map-layer', 'children')],
    [Input('data-source', 'value'),
     Input('station-dropdown', 'value'),
     Input('x-column-dropdown', 'value'),
     Input('time-dropdown', 'value')]
)
def update_output(data_source, stations, x_column, time_value):
    df = df_year_location if data_source == 'year' else df_season_location if data_source == 'season' else df_month_location
    if data_source != 'year':
        df = df[df[data_source] == time_value] if time_value else df

    df = df[df['station_id'].isin(stations)] if stations else df
    avg_values = df.groupby('station_id')[x_column].mean().reset_index()

    # Update graph
    figure = {
        'data': [{'x': avg_values['station_id'], 'y': avg_values[x_column], 'type': 'bar'}],
        'layout': {'title': f'Average {x_column}'}
    }

    # Update map markers
    markers = [dl.Marker(position=[row['Latitude'], row['Longitude']],
                         children=dl.Tooltip(f"{row['station_id']}: {row[x_column]:.2f}"))
               for _, row in avg_values.merge(df, on='station_id').drop_duplicates(subset=['station_id']).iterrows()]

    return figure, markers

# Callback to update description
@app.callback(
    Output('description', 'children'),
    [Input('x-column-dropdown', 'value')]
)
def update_description(selected_x_column):
    return x_column_descriptions.get(selected_x_column, "No description available.")

    app.run_server(debug=True)
